{"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/EnsemblesEncrypted\/documentation\/EnsemblesEncrypted"},"metadata":{"title":"EnsemblesEncrypted","modules":[{"name":"EnsemblesEncrypted"}],"role":"collection","externalID":"EnsemblesEncrypted","roleHeading":"Framework","symbolKind":"module"},"kind":"symbol","primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Overview","level":2,"anchor":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"EnsemblesEncrypted provides "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/EnsemblesEncrypted\/documentation\/EnsemblesEncrypted\/EncryptedCloudFileSystem","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":", a wrapper that encrypts files before uploading and decrypts after downloading. It can wrap any "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CloudFileSystem"},{"type":"text","text":" implementation — CloudKit, Google Drive, WebDAV, or your own custom backend — to provide end-to-end encryption for sync data."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Encrypted files are stored in a password-derived vault directory with a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".cdecrypt"},{"type":"text","text":" extension. This is backward compatible with the Ensembles 2 Objective-C "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CDEEncryptedCloudFileSystem"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"heading","text":"Encryption Formats","level":3,"anchor":"Encryption-Formats"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Two encryption formats are available:"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":".modern"}]},{"type":"text","text":" (default) — AES-256-GCM. Fast, authenticated encryption using Apple’s CryptoKit. Recommended for new apps."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":".legacy"}]},{"type":"text","text":" — RNCryptor v3 format. Use this for backward compatibility with Ensembles 2 encrypted data."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The backend auto-detects the encryption format when downloading, so a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".modern"},{"type":"text","text":" client can read "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".legacy"},{"type":"text","text":" files and vice versa. The format setting only controls how "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"new","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" files are encrypted."}]},{"type":"heading","text":"Setup","level":3,"anchor":"Setup"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Wrap any cloud file system with encryption:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["import Ensembles","import EnsemblesEncrypted","import EnsemblesCloudKit","","\/\/ Wrap CloudKit with encryption","let cloudKitFS = CloudKitFileSystem(","    ubiquityContainerIdentifier: \"iCloud.com.yourcompany.yourapp\"",")","let encryptedFS = EncryptedCloudFileSystem(","    cloudFileSystem: cloudKitFS,","    password: \"user-supplied-password\"",")","","let ensemble = CoreDataEnsemble(","    ensembleIdentifier: \"MainStore\",","    persistentStoreURL: storeURL,","    managedObjectModelURL: modelURL,","    cloudFileSystem: encryptedFS!",")","try await ensemble?.attachPersistentStore()"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For more control over the vault, use the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"VaultInfo"},{"type":"text","text":" initializer:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["let encryptedFS = EncryptedCloudFileSystem(","    cloudFileSystem: innerFS,","    vaultInfo: vaultInfo,","    encryptionFormat: .modern",")"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"heading","text":"When to Use Encryption","level":3,"anchor":"When-to-Use-Encryption"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Ensembles sync data is stored as opaque binary files, so even without encryption the raw data is not human-readable. However, it could be deserialized by someone with access to your cloud storage."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"CloudKit","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":", Apple encrypts "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CKAsset"},{"type":"text","text":" data at rest. With Advanced Data Protection (ADP) enabled, assets are end-to-end encrypted. Wrapping CloudKit with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"EncryptedCloudFileSystem"},{"type":"text","text":" adds a layer of protection that doesn’t depend on the user enabling ADP."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"third-party backends","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" (Google Drive, OneDrive, WebDAV, etc.), the storage provider can see the raw files. Wrapping with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"EncryptedCloudFileSystem"},{"type":"text","text":" ensures data is encrypted before it leaves the device, regardless of what the provider does."}]},{"type":"heading","text":"How It Works","level":3,"anchor":"How-It-Works"},{"type":"orderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Vault directory"}]},{"type":"text","text":" — All encrypted files are stored inside a vault directory in the cloud, derived from the password. Different passwords create different vaults, so the same cloud account can host multiple independent encrypted sync stores."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Upload"}]},{"type":"text","text":" — When Ensembles uploads a file, the wrapper encrypts it to a local temporary file, uploads the encrypted version with a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".cdecrypt"},{"type":"text","text":" extension, then removes the temporary file."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Download"}]},{"type":"text","text":" — When Ensembles downloads a file, the wrapper downloads the encrypted "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".cdecrypt"},{"type":"text","text":" file, auto-detects the format (modern or legacy), decrypts it to a local temporary file, and returns the decrypted content."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Backward compatibility"}]},{"type":"text","text":" — The "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".legacy"},{"type":"text","text":" format uses RNCryptor v3, the same encryption format used by Ensembles 2’s "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CDEEncryptedCloudFileSystem"},{"type":"text","text":". Apps migrating from E2 to E3 can read existing encrypted cloud data without re-encrypting."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"type":"heading","text":"Wrapping Other Backends","level":3,"anchor":"Wrapping-Other-Backends"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The wrapper works with any "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CloudFileSystem"},{"type":"text","text":":"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["\/\/ Wrap Google Drive","let encryptedGDrive = EncryptedCloudFileSystem(","    cloudFileSystem: GoogleDriveCloudFileSystem(authenticator: gdAuthenticator),","    password: password",")","","\/\/ Wrap WebDAV","let encryptedWebDAV = EncryptedCloudFileSystem(","    cloudFileSystem: WebDAVCloudFileSystem(baseURL: webdavURL, username: user, password: pass),","    password: encryptionPassword",")"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"heading","text":"Dependencies","level":3,"anchor":"Dependencies"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This module has "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"no external dependencies","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" beyond Foundation, CryptoKit, and the core "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Ensembles"},{"type":"text","text":" framework."}]}],"kind":"content"}],"sections":[],"topicSections":[{"title":"Cloud File System","anchor":"Cloud-File-System","identifiers":["doc:\/\/EnsemblesEncrypted\/documentation\/EnsemblesEncrypted\/EncryptedCloudFileSystem"]},{"title":"Structures","generated":true,"anchor":"Structures","identifiers":["doc:\/\/EnsemblesEncrypted\/documentation\/EnsemblesEncrypted\/VaultInfo"]},{"title":"Enumerations","generated":true,"anchor":"Enumerations","identifiers":["doc:\/\/EnsemblesEncrypted\/documentation\/EnsemblesEncrypted\/EncryptionError","doc:\/\/EnsemblesEncrypted\/documentation\/EnsemblesEncrypted\/EncryptionFormat","doc:\/\/EnsemblesEncrypted\/documentation\/EnsemblesEncrypted\/FileEncryptor"]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"patch":0,"minor":3},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"An encryption wrapper for any Ensembles cloud backend."}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/ensemblesencrypted"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[[]]},"references":{"doc://EnsemblesEncrypted/documentation/EnsemblesEncrypted/VaultInfo":{"kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"VaultInfo","kind":"identifier"}],"url":"\/documentation\/ensemblesencrypted\/vaultinfo","type":"topic","abstract":[{"text":"Represents a vault in an encrypted cloud file system.","type":"text"}],"title":"VaultInfo","identifier":"doc:\/\/EnsemblesEncrypted\/documentation\/EnsemblesEncrypted\/VaultInfo","role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"VaultInfo","kind":"identifier"}]},"doc://EnsemblesEncrypted/documentation/EnsemblesEncrypted":{"url":"\/documentation\/ensemblesencrypted","title":"EnsemblesEncrypted","identifier":"doc:\/\/EnsemblesEncrypted\/documentation\/EnsemblesEncrypted","role":"collection","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"An encryption wrapper for any Ensembles cloud backend."}],"type":"topic","kind":"symbol"},"doc://EnsemblesEncrypted/documentation/EnsemblesEncrypted/EncryptionError":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/EnsemblesEncrypted\/documentation\/EnsemblesEncrypted\/EncryptionError","kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"EncryptionError","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Errors that can occur during encryption or decryption."}],"type":"topic","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"enum"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"EncryptionError"}],"title":"EncryptionError","url":"\/documentation\/ensemblesencrypted\/encryptionerror"},"doc://EnsemblesEncrypted/documentation/EnsemblesEncrypted/EncryptedCloudFileSystem":{"url":"\/documentation\/ensemblesencrypted\/encryptedcloudfilesystem","title":"EncryptedCloudFileSystem","identifier":"doc:\/\/EnsemblesEncrypted\/documentation\/EnsemblesEncrypted\/EncryptedCloudFileSystem","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"EncryptedCloudFileSystem","kind":"identifier"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"EncryptedCloudFileSystem"}],"abstract":[{"text":"A cloud file system wrapper that encrypts files before uploading","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"and decrypts them after downloading.","type":"text"}],"type":"topic","kind":"symbol"},"doc://EnsemblesEncrypted/documentation/EnsemblesEncrypted/EncryptionFormat":{"url":"\/documentation\/ensemblesencrypted\/encryptionformat","title":"EncryptionFormat","identifier":"doc:\/\/EnsemblesEncrypted\/documentation\/EnsemblesEncrypted\/EncryptionFormat","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"enum","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"EncryptionFormat","kind":"identifier"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"EncryptionFormat","kind":"identifier"}],"type":"topic","abstract":[{"text":"The encryption format to use when encrypting data.","type":"text"}],"kind":"symbol"},"doc://EnsemblesEncrypted/documentation/EnsemblesEncrypted/FileEncryptor":{"title":"FileEncryptor","identifier":"doc:\/\/EnsemblesEncrypted\/documentation\/EnsemblesEncrypted\/FileEncryptor","type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Unified encryption\/decryption interface with automatic format detection on decrypt."}],"kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"enum","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"FileEncryptor","kind":"identifier"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"FileEncryptor","kind":"identifier"}],"url":"\/documentation\/ensemblesencrypted\/fileencryptor","role":"symbol"}}}